Combine the broccoli, onion, ham and cheese; set aside. In a mixing bowl, beat eggs until frothy. Add oil; mix well. Combine dry ingredients; add to the egg mixture just until moistened. Fold in broccoli mixture. Fill greased muffin cups two-thirds full. Bake at 375 degrees F for 18-22 minutes or until muffins test done. Cool for 10 minutes; remove from pan to a wire rack.